<div id="review_1778840843" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1778840843" />
    <a title="Michael Finocchiaro" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48483884-michael-finocchiaro"><img alt="Michael Finocchiaro" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576692048p2/48483884.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1778840843?book_show_action=true">Oct 08, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Finocchiaro" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Finocchiaro" href="/user/show/48483884-michael-finocchiaro">Michael Finocchiaro</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=french-18th-c">french-18th-c</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=novels">novels</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=read-in-french">read-in-french</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/48483884-michael-finocchiaro?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1778840843" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5301425337287151640">Voltaire had a unique sense of satire and his Zadig character is one of the great ones - sort of a 17th century Forrest Gump. The other stories in this collection all feel a bit dated, and none reach the quality of Zadig in this reader&apos;s opinion. It remains, with Candide, one of Voltaire&apos;s signature works of fiction. It takes place in ancient Babylonia and barely disguises the satirical portraits of the courtiers that Voltaire is parodying while in exile in Amsterdam in 1748. Curiously enough, i</span>
  <span id="freeText5301425337287151640" style="display:none">Voltaire had a unique sense of satire and his Zadig character is one of the great ones - sort of a 17th century Forrest Gump. The other stories in this collection all feel a bit dated, and none reach the quality of Zadig in this reader's opinion. It remains, with Candide, one of Voltaire's signature works of fiction. It takes place in ancient Babylonia and barely disguises the satirical portraits of the courtiers that Voltaire is parodying while in exile in Amsterdam in 1748. Curiously enough, it was cited as an inspiration to writers as different as Arthur Conan Doyle, Sade, and Edgar Allen Poe. Definitely worth the time to seek out and read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5301425337287151640" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


