              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2901200489895061821">Zadig and his series of misfortune events. I found this story is slightly have such similarity with Don Quixote. Zadig, the protagonist who lived in Babylonian time, told a story of the story of a man with his best effort to help one to another. He helped a fisherman from a suicidal issue, he gave advices and spoke brutal truths. <br/><br/>Zadig was just a genuine guy, yet when he tried to do something good or being nice to others, it seemed attract the opposite sides, such as jealousy and ignorance. I ac</span>
  <span id="freeText2901200489895061821" style="display:none">Zadig and his series of misfortune events. I found this story is slightly have such similarity with Don Quixote. Zadig, the protagonist who lived in Babylonian time, told a story of the story of a man with his best effort to help one to another. He helped a fisherman from a suicidal issue, he gave advices and spoke brutal truths. <br /><br />Zadig was just a genuine guy, yet when he tried to do something good or being nice to others, it seemed attract the opposite sides, such as jealousy and ignorance. I acknowledged it as part of the seven deadly sins of human being characters. A masterpiece of Voltaire that one have to read it.</span>
