<div id="review_2274878974" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2274878974" />
    <a title="Laurie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/804276-laurie"><img alt="Laurie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1482536929p2/804276.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2274878974?book_show_action=true">Jan 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laurie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laurie" href="/user/show/804276-laurie">Laurie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/804276-laurie?shelf=2018">2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/804276-laurie?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2274878974" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15554869704544081572">Like Voltaire&apos;s Candide, this is an adventure story of a good guy experiencing a lot of rough luck. In this very short philosophical novel, instead of an optimist against non-stop tragedy, this tale takes a decent, hardworking, ethical, intelligent philosopher and pits him against hardship in which he both wins and loses in Ancient Babylonia. He learns lessons of destiny and fate. Candide is Voltaire&apos;s most well known and read work, but I think I liked this one just a little better than Candide.</span>
  <span id="freeText15554869704544081572" style="display:none">Like Voltaire's Candide, this is an adventure story of a good guy experiencing a lot of rough luck. In this very short philosophical novel, instead of an optimist against non-stop tragedy, this tale takes a decent, hardworking, ethical, intelligent philosopher and pits him against hardship in which he both wins and loses in Ancient Babylonia. He learns lessons of destiny and fate. Candide is Voltaire's most well known and read work, but I think I liked this one just a little better than Candide.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15554869704544081572" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


